rComments: Pretty good lecturer, although he rarely went along with the book.

Get a bunch of friends in the class with you.  Then alternate and have one person fill out all the attendance quizzes.  Lectures are pointless.  Read the book, lecture notes, and go to discussion.  I pulled a B in the class and didn't go to lecture after the midterm.  Tests are approximately 75% book and 25% lecture/discussion.  Get an english TA.

Easy class. Tests are 100 times easier than Gottiel. Lectures are filled with boring left winged economics. Tests are 70-80 MC questions, very basic entry level stuff. You do all the learning on your own. Most of the lectures don't correlate with the readings. About 15-20 of the questions are from lecture/online lecture notes.

He's okay as a teacher. Just make sure that your TA speaks english. They were right about the book stuff not really relating to his lectures. Tests are 30% lecture though, so go or look online for the notes. Those darn sweaters he wears distracted me for the most part...

I didn't learn anything in this class.  I felt like lectures didn't have anything to do with the material in the book.  Somehow I still got an A, but I felt like I didn't know where I stood the whole semester.
easiest class I have ever taken by far. aced it so easily
Not very clear on material in class but tests are straight forward.
